cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D object recognition using deep neural networks. The use of multi-view images and 3D convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of 3D max-pooling layers suggests that it could belong to the neural networks and learning (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the experiments on real-world scenarios suggest that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
